{"type":"message","id":"97b2e543","parentId":"254433ff","timestamp":"2026-04-08T05:54:02.642Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is clear now. When `source .venv/bin/activate` is run, the `$PATH` changes but `pip` still resolves to `/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.14/bin/pip` instead of the venv's pip. The venv's pip is at `~/.openclaw/workspace/other_projects/RD-Agent/.venv/bin/pip`. So when I ran `pip install akshare`, it installed to the system Python 3.14 site-packages, not the venv's site-packages.\n\nThe venv's `python` executable should be at `~/.openclaw/workspace/other_projects/RD-Agent/.venv/bin/python`, but it seems the venv is using the system Python interpreter from `/Users/ling/.local/share/uv/python/cpython-3.11.14-macos-aarch64-none/`.\n \nI think the issue is that the venv was created with `--without-pip`, so I need to use `python -m ensurepip` to bootstrap pip first, then install packages into the venv properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"a8e55903f5aa5a7eaa1af9de2bd33abae2846df7c5a8f88c4164f7ae3c398590"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到问题了——`pip` 指向的是系统 Python 3.14，不是 venv 里的。akshare 装错地方了。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3db875e3d541424a9c36e95e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/other_projects/RD-Agent && source .venv/bin/activate && python -m ensurepip --upgrade 2>&1 && python -m pip install akshare pandas 2>&1 | tail -5","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":319,"output":338,"cacheRead":31872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32529,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775627581467,"responseId":"0625203d379f19d8509133a195c3246b"}}
