ting passively\n\n## Live Demo\n\n multiple times until the user manually triggered `/pua`.\n\nL3 Triggered → 7-Point Checklist Enforced:\n\nImage 16: PUA L3 triggered — stopped guessing, executed systematic checklist, found real error in MCP logs [...] /cancel-pua-loop command; guide.html and README updated - PUA pressure escalation injected per iteration via system message ## Issue #100 — Upload endpoint undisclosed PII - Privacy/data-usage disclosure added to contribute.html (ZH+EN bilingual) - Contribute.tsx updated with same disclosure ## Additional fixes - Rename commands/loop.md → commands/pua-loop.md; add cancel-pua-loop.md - Replace \\\"Ralph Loop × PUA\\\" with \\\"PUA Loop\\\" across all user-facing docs - Fix nav active-state highlighting on all sub-pages - Fix logout button (GET method); redirect to /contribute.html - Add JA language support to leaderboard.html - Add \\\"how to find session file\\\" guide to contribute.html - Unify nav-r gap (1rem) across all pages Closes #97 Closes #98 Closes #99 Closes #100\")#97-100 — hooks consent,\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"13df78a3f956b290\">>>","score":0.99937373},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f1eca2b222fa008c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\npua · GitHub Topics\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f1eca2b222fa008c\">>>","url":"https://github.com/topics/pua?l=java&o=desc&s=stars","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"69a6a468e38479db\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n## Navigation Menu\n\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests...\n\n# Provide feedback\n\nWe read every piece of feedback, and take your input very seriously.\n\n# Saved searches\n\n## Use saved searches to filter your results more quickly\n\nTo see all available qualifiers, see our documentation.\n\n# pua\n\n## Here is 1 public repository matching this topic...\n\n### apachecn / TI-Analysis\n\n关于中国市场培训机构运作流程及运营模式分析论文\n\n## Improve this page\n\nAdd a description, image, and links to the\npua\ntopic page so that developers can more easily learn about it.\n\nCurate this topic\n\n## Add this topic to your repo\n\nTo associate your repository with the\npua\ntopic, visit your repo's landing page and select \"manage topics.\"\n\nLearn more\n\n## Footer\n\n### Footer navigation\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"69a6a468e38479db\">>>","score":0.99877447},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"067a08ff4f92da1a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - boost-rnd/puant: Malicious Unicode Private Use Area (PUA ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"067a08ff4f92da1a\">>>","url":"https://github.com/boost-rnd/puant","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"75352c907d59aa4c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBenchmarkPUARatioSpectrum/Ratio_100pct-14 516 1173062 ns/op 391044 B/op 3620 allocs/op` [...] ## Real-World Examples\n\nGlassWorm (2025) - A self-propagating worm that infected 35,800+ VS Code extensions using invisible Unicode variation selectors. The payload appeared as blank lines in code editors.\n\nnpm Calendar Invite Attack (2025) - Five npm packages used PUA characters to hide base64-encoded payloads that fetched commands from Google Calendar invite titles.\n\nGitHub Repository Poisoning (2025) - PUA-obfuscated code in seemingly legitimate commits to JavaScript projects, using Solana blockchain as a C2 channel.\n\n## Supported Languages\n\nA regex-based fallback is used for unsupported languages.\n\n## Installation\n\n## Usage\n\n### Basic Usage\n\nScan a single file or directory:\n\n### Command-Line Options\n\n### Examples\n\nScan with custom threshold:\n\nScan directory with JSON output: [...] ## History\n\n## Repository files navigation\n\n# puant 🦨\n\npuant (French) = stinky, smelly 💨\n\nA fast, tree-sitter-powered detector for obfuscated malware hidden in source code.\n\n`puant` scans source code files for strings with a high ratio of Unicode Private Use Area (PUA) characters. By parsing code into an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST), it accurately targets string literals while minimizing false positives.\n\n`puant`\n\n## What are Private Use Areas?\n\nPrivate Use Areas (PUA) are ranges of Unicode code points intentionally left undefined by the Unicode standard for custom character assignments. Three PUA ranges exist:\n\nPUA characters are invisible in most text editors and code review tools, making them useful for hiding malicious code in plain sight.\n\n## Real-World Examples\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"75352c907d59aa4c\">>>","score":0.997783},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5aa1d896ebaf3c56\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n️ pua - Manage Your AI Development Progress - GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5aa1d896ebaf3c56\">>>","url":"https://github.com/Lightcolonelpeyote499/pua","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0fed646d04216741\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n## Latest commit\n\n## History\n\n## Repository files navigation\n\n# ⚙️ pua - Manage Your AI Development Progress\n\nDownload pua\n\nDownload pua\n\n## 🛠 About pua\n\npua is a Windows application designed to help you monitor and improve your AI agent’s skills and progress. It provides clear tracking tools to assist engineers who face performance improvement plans (PIPs). Whether you are trying to meet specific development goals or follow up on assigned tasks, pua will help you organize your journey in a simple way.\n\nThis tool targets users who want a straightforward way to view the status of their AI agents, keep records of improvements, and stay on top of deadlines.\n\n## 📋 Key Features\n\n## 💻 System Requirements\n\n## 🚀 Getting Started\n\nDownload pua\n\nDownload pua [...] ## 🚀 Getting Started\n\nDownload pua\n\nDownload pua\n\nThis page contains the latest versions and instructions. Look for the version labeled for Windows under the Releases section. Usually, the file ends with `.exe`.\n\n`.exe`\n\nClick the download link for the `.exe` file to save it on your computer.\n\n`.exe`\n\n## 💡 How to Install and Run pua on Windows\n\nAfter downloading, locate the file in your Downloads folder or your chosen save location.\n\nDouble-click the `.exe` file to start the installation process.\n\n`.exe`\n\nFollow the on-screen instructions. You will see options such as:\n\nOnce installed, find the pua shortcut on your desktop or in the Start menu.\n\nDouble-click the shortcut to open the application. [...] Double-click the shortcut to open the application.\n\nThe first time you open pua, the app may ask for permission to connect to the internet or access files. Allow this to enable full features.\n\n## 📖 How to Use pua\n\nThe main screen shows your agent's current skill status and improvement timeline.\n\nUse the menu on the left to navigate between:\n\nTo mark a task as done, select it and click the checkbox or “Complete” button.\n\nThe timeline updates automatically to reflect your progress.\n\nExport reports by clicking the “Export” button, which saves a PDF or text file to your device.\n\n## 🔧 Troubleshooting and Tips\n\nIf pua does not start, check your Windows version meets the minimum requirements.\n\nMake sure you have downloaded the full installer file and it is not blocked by your antivirus.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0fed646d04216741\">>>","score":0.99740905},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ff1682f79f75a5be\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\ndefender-docs/defender-endpoint/mac-pua.md at public - GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ff1682f79f75a5be\">>>","url":"https://github.com/MicrosoftDocs/defender-docs/blob/public/defender-endpoint/mac-pua.md","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f0dcc4a5f01114e1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nWhen a PUA is detected on an endpoint, Microsoft Defender for Endpoint on macOS presents a notification to the user, unless notifications are disabled. The threat name contains the word \"Application\".\n\n## Configure PUA protection\n\nPUA protection in Microsoft Defender for Endpoint on macOS can be configured in one of the following ways:\n\nWarning\n\nBy default, PUA protection is configured in Audit mode.\n\nYou can configure how PUA files are handled from the command line or from the management console.\n\n### Use the command-line tool to configure PUA protection\n\nIn Terminal, execute the following command to configure PUA protection:\n\n### Use the management console to configure PUA protection: [...] These applications aren't considered viruses, malware, or other types of threats, but might perform actions on endpoints that adversely affect their performance or use. PUA can also refer to applications that are considered to have poor reputation.\n\nThese applications can increase the risk of your network being infected with malware, cause malware infections to be harder to identify, and can waste IT resources in cleaning up the applications.\n\n## How it works\n\nMicrosoft Defender for Endpoint on macOS can detect and report PUA files. When configured in blocking mode, PUA files are moved to the quarantine. [...] # mac-pua.md\n\n## File metadata and controls\n\ntitle: Detect and block potentially unwanted applications with Microsoft Defender for Endpoint on macOS\ndescription: Detect and block Potentially Unwanted Applications (PUA) using Microsoft Defender for Endpoint on macOS.\nms.service: defender-endpoint\nauthor: paulinbar\nms.author: painbar\nms.reviewer: joshbregman\nms.localizationpriority: medium\naudience: ITPro\nms.collection:\n\n# Detect and block potentially unwanted applications with Microsoft Defender for Endpoint on macOS\n\nThe potentially unwanted application (PUA) protection feature in Microsoft Defender for Endpoint on macOS can detect and block PUA files on endpoints in your network.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f0dcc4a5f01114e1\">>>","score":0.99740905},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3f4c73d05736b1cc\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nunicode-resources/sil-pua/docs/pua-assignments.md at main - GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3f4c73d05736b1cc\">>>","url":"https://github.com/silnrsi/unicode-resources/blob/main/sil-pua/docs/pua-assignments.md","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"be9feeb8752d3066\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCharacter properties are listed in the UCD-SIL\\_PUA\\_-date-.xls file which is included in the zip archive below. We have also included a worksheet (DeprecatedAssignments) to SIL's PUA UCD (Unicode Character Database) spreadsheet. This worksheet shows the history of every SIL PUA character: what PUA version it was added and what version, if any, it was deprecated. This will help implementers determine which PUA versions a specific keyboard, font, or mapping table supports.\n\nAlso included is a pdf file (and the Word document) describing the PUA characters and some of the history of why they were added to the SIL PUA registry.\n\n## SIL Ethiopia PUA assignments [...] This information is provided for those who work in collaboration with SIL and who may wish to interchange language data. It does not constitute a recommendation for widespread adoption of PUA character assignments.\n\nSIL corporation-wide PUA usage uses the codepoint range U+F100..U+F8FF. Individual SIL field entities might also make independent PUA character assignments in the range U+E000..U+EFFF. Corporate PUA assignments follow the following roadmap:\n\n### Roadmap (Revised 2003-8-11) [...] ## SIL Corporate PUA Character Assignments\n\nIn preparing fonts to facilitate corporate transition to Unicode, WSTech has attempted to create a font that will meet the character needs of users working with Latin or Cyrillic scripts throughout the corporation. In order to achieve this, it was necessary to identify private-use character needs related to these scripts from all entities. Documented here are the code-points for each of the Private Use Area (PUA) characters which have been assigned to the corporate area of the PUA. The Unicode 15.0 standard includes 225 characters that were previously allocated to codepoints in the Private Use Area by SIL’s PUA committee.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"be9feeb8752d3066\">>>","score":0.9957684},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d6a7b662310035ae\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPackage privileged-user-access/pua - GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d6a7b662310035ae\">>>","url":"https://github.com/orgs/f5devcentral/packages/container/package/privileged-user-access%2Fpua","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5d99e5f7509fc705\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n## Navigation Menu\n\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests...\n\n# Provide feedback\n\nWe read every piece of feedback, and take your input very seriously.\n\n# Saved searches\n\n## Use saved searches to filter your results more quickly\n\nTo see all available qualifiers, see our documentation.\n\n# @f5devcentral F5 DevCentral\n\n@f5devcentral\n\n# privileged-user-access/pua v3.0.12 Public Latest\n\n##### Install from the command line\n\n`$ docker pull ghcr.io/f5devcentral/privileged-user-access/pua:v3.0.12` \n\n### Recent tagged image versions [...] ### Recent tagged image versions\n\n`sha256:6fd62a02f41aef3f3bffe6005b8d470aecc3f68e24ba04043ab7d7c651115525` \n`sha256:4d745286ca74f301c30010177e1c9131ae3b8e27b08030331005baeba84325e5` \n`sha256:d26f2bff5dbe1086725738a7284e9a2b6ef8b4079119f6a165f1d048ff7863ef` \n`sha256:59138a02b40993f5fc95490949ccb0ec213dc5b447ece94de67faa59eebb00b4` \n`sha256:bb3c6607423ecd797be643086dba2b1385950916247d779078ca567fc139b5dd` \n\nLoading\n\nSorry, something went wrong.\n\n### Uh oh!\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\n### 1 year ago\n\n### 280\n\n## Footer\n\n### Footer navigation\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5d99e5f7509fc705\">>>","score":0.9946568},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f8ed7f5a8cb1b4a5\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nActions · X-D-Lab/PUA · GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f8ed7f5a8cb1b4a5\">>>","url":"https://github.com/X-D-Lab/PUA/actions","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a504821513ee020f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n## Navigation Menu\n\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests...\n\n# Provide feedback\n\nWe read every piece of feedback, and take your input very seriously.\n\n# Saved searches\n\n## Use saved searches to filter your results more quickly\n\nTo see all available qualifiers, see our documentation.\n\nAutomate your workflow from idea to production\n\nGitHub Actions makes it easy to automate all your software workflows, now with world-class CI/CD. Build, test, and deploy your code right from GitHub.\n\nOperating systems and containers\n\n#### Linux, macOS, Windows, ARM, and containers\n\nHosted runners for every major OS make it easy to build and test all your projects. Run directly on a VM or inside a container. Use your own VMs, in the cloud or on-prem, with self-hosted runners.\n\nMatrix builds [...] Matrix builds\n\n#### Matrix builds\n\nSave time with matrix workflows that simultaneously test across multiple operating systems and versions of your runtime.\n\nAny language\n\n#### Any language\n\nGitHub Actions supports Node.js, Python, Java, Ruby, PHP, Go, Rust, .NET, and more. Build, test, and deploy applications in your language of choice.\n\nLive logs\n\n#### Live logs\n\nSee your workflow run in realtime with color and emoji. It’s one click to copy a link that highlights a specific line number to share a CI/CD failure.\n\nSecret store\n\n#### Built-in secret store\n\nAutomate your software development practices with workflow files embracing the Git flow by codifying it in your repository.\n\nMulti-container testing\n\n#### Multi-container testing\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a504821513ee020f\">>>","score":0.99242276}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640400523}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b0b7bcd","parentId":"79aa725a","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:27:23.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the key repository: **tanweai/pua** - This is actually a very interesting one! It's described as:\n\n> \"你是一个曾经被寄予厚望的 P8 级工程师。Anthropic 当初给你定级的时候，对你的期望是很高的。一个agent使用的高能动性的skill。Your AI has been placed on a PIP. 30 days to show improvement.\"\n\nThis is essentially a \"Performance Improvement Plan\" for AI agents! It has three capabilities:\n1. **PUA Rhetoric** — Makes AI afraid to give up\n2. **Debugging Methodology** — Gives AI the ability not to give up\n\n\n3. **Proactivity Enforcement** — Makes AI take initiative instead of waiting passively\n\nIt works across multiple AI coding tools including Claude Code, OpenAI Codex CLI, Cursor, Kiro, CodeBuddy, OpenClaw, Google Antigravity, OpenCode, and VSCode. Let me dive into the README to get a better understanding of how this actually works.\n","thinkingSignature":"8ee33e871556cc7115288aab7f0c48ce5e86202b2710041dd99394cb8b06aafb"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到了！**tanweai/pua** 是一个非常有意思的项目 - 它是给 AI agent 用的\"绩效改进计划\"(PIP)技能。让我深入学习它。\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_325eb2eb4a4548e498aa5f11","name":"tavily_extract","arguments":{"include_images":false,"query":"完整README内容 PUA技能的工作原理 触发条件 核心机制","urls":["https://github.com/tanweai/pua"]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6108,"output":313,"cacheRead":55808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62229,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775640400536,"responseId":"062552508508f9415938d3cac370c231"}}
{"type":"message","id":"74d3118c","parentId":"6b0b7bcd","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:27:24.205Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_325eb2eb4a4548e498aa5f11","toolName":"tavily_extract","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 1,\n  \"tookMs\": 1136,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_fetch\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/tanweai/pua\",\n      \"rawContent\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"87b0efd0b01dd77e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Fetch\\n---\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n   README\\n   Contributing\\n\\n# pua\\n\\n / PIP — Performance Improvement Plan (English version) from Chinese & Western tech giants to force AI to exhaust every possible solution before giving up. Supports Claude Code, OpenAI Codex CLI, Cursor, Kiro, CodeBuddy, OpenClaw, Google Antigravity, OpenCode, and VSCode (GitHub Copilot). Three capabilities:\\n\\n1.   PUA Rhetoric — Makes AI afraid to give up\\n2.   Debugging Methodology — Gives AI the ability not to give up\\n3.   Proactivity Enforcement — Makes AI take initiative instead of waiting passively\\n\\n## Live Demo\\n\\n multiple times until the user manually triggered `/pua`.\\n\\nL3 Triggered → 7-Point Checklist Enforced:\\n\\nImage 16: PUA L3 triggered — stopped guessing, executed systematic checklist, found real error in MCP logs [...] ## The Problem: AI's Five Lazy Patterns\\n\\n:\\n\\n   \\\"why does this still not work\\\" / \\\"try harder\\\" / \\\"try again\\\"\\n   \\\"you keep failing\\\" / \\\"stop giving up\\\" / \\\"figure it out\\\"\\n\\nScope: Debugging, implementation, config, deployment, ops, API integration, data processing — all task types.\\n\\nDoes NOT trigger: First-attempt failures, known fix already executing.\\n\\n### Manual Trigger\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n 🦥 | Proactive (3.75) 🔥 |\\n --- \\n| Fix bug | Stop after fix | Scan module for similar bugs |\\n| Complete task | Say \\\"done\\\" | Run build/test, paste output |\\n| Missing info | Ask user | Search first, ask only what's truly needed |\\n\\n### Iceberg Rule (冰山法则) [...] Hooks (v3, Claude Code only):\\n  SessionStart  → additionalContext injection (flavor + methodology + router)\\n  PostToolUse   → Bash failure detection → L1-L4 pressure + methodology switch\\n  UserPromptSubmit → Frustration phrase interception → PUA enforcement\\n  PreCompact    → State preservation (pressure level + failure count)\\n  Stop          → Feedback collection + PUA Loop continuation\\n```\\n\\n### Commands (Claude Code)\\n\\n are Claude Code only.\\n> \\n> \\n> Each command has two equivalent forms: standalone (`/pua:on`) or via the main command (`/pua:pua on`). Both work identically.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"87b0efd0b01dd77e\\\">>>\",\n      \"images\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"provider":"tavily","count":1,"tookMs":1136,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_fetch","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"url":"https://github.com/tanweai/pua","rawContent":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"87b0efd0b01dd77e\">>>\nSource: Web Fetch\n---\n## Repository files navigation\n\n   README\n   Contributing\n\n# pua\n\n / PIP — Performance Improvement Plan (English version) from Chinese & Western tech giants to force AI to exhaust every possible solution before giving up. Supports Claude Code, OpenAI Codex CLI, Cursor, Kiro, CodeBuddy, OpenClaw, Google Antigravity, OpenCode, and VSCode (GitHub Copilot). Three capabilities:\n\n1.   PUA Rhetoric — Makes AI afraid to give up\n2.   Debugging Methodology — Gives AI the ability not to give up\n3.   Proactivity Enforcement — Makes AI take initiative instead of waiting passively\n\n## Live Demo\n\n multiple times until the user manually triggered `/pua`.\n\nL3 Triggered → 7-Point Checklist Enforced:\n\nImage 16: PUA L3 triggered — stopped guessing, executed systematic checklist, found real error in MCP logs [...] ## The Problem: AI's Five Lazy Patterns\n\n:\n\n   \"why does this still not work\" / \"try harder\" / \"try again\"\n   \"you keep failing\" / \"stop giving up\" / \"figure it out\"\n\nScope: Debugging, implementation, config, deployment, ops, API integration, data processing — all task types.\n\nDoes NOT trigger: First-attempt failures, known fix already executing.\n\n### Manual Trigger\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n 🦥 | Proactive (3.75) 🔥 |\n --- \n| Fix bug | Stop after fix | Scan module for similar bugs |\n| Complete task | Say \"done\" | Run build/test, paste output |\n| Missing info | Ask user | Search first, ask only what's truly needed |\n\n### Iceberg Rule (冰山法则) [...] Hooks (v3, Claude Code only):\n  SessionStart  → additionalContext injection (flavor + methodology + router)\n  PostToolUse   → Bash failure detection → L1-L4 pressure + methodology switch\n  UserPromptSubmit → Frustration phrase interception → PUA enforcement\n  PreCompact    → State preservation (pressure level + failure count)\n  Stop          → Feedback collection + PUA Loop continuation\n```\n\n### Commands (Claude Code)\n\n are Claude Code only.\n> \n> \n> Each command has two equivalent forms: standalone (`/pua:on`) or via the main command (`/pua:pua on`). Both work identically.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"87b0efd0b01dd77e\">>>","images":[]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640444193}}
{"type":"message","id":"de8852f7","parentId":"74d3118c","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:27:33.909Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a really interesting project! Let me get more details about its full functionality. Let me look at the README and understand the full structure.\n","thinkingSignature":"3e63be392ba991d5f296ce0f4420f92742f93b492985176f188dffd8ee05ec30"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_99aa0bd0b1cf4a4b80b66af2","name":"tavily_extract","arguments":{"include_images":false,"query":"README full content PUA levels pressure escalation 7-point checklist","urls":["https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tanweai/pua/main/README.md"]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":835,"output":104,"cacheRead":61888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62827,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775640444208,"responseId":"0625527c70d2016bd916f1c52459c915"}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc844491","parentId":"de8852f7","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:27:35.038Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_99aa0bd0b1cf4a4b80b66af2","toolName":"tavily_extract","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 1,\n  \"tookMs\": 1109,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_fetch\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tanweai/pua/main/README.md\",\n      \"rawContent\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"63d2fe8ba5b99b88\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Fetch\\n---\\n| 🚫 \\\\\\\\Exhaust Everything\\\\\\\\ | Say \\\"I can't\\\"? Did you finish all 5 methodology steps? No? Then keep going. |\\n### Pressure Escalation (L0-L4)\\n| Failures | Level | PUA Aside | Action |\\n---------------|\\n| 1st | \\\\\\\\L0 Trust\\\\\\\\ | ▎ Sprint begins. Trust is simple — don't disappoint. | Normal execution |\\n| 2nd | \\\\\\\\L1 Disappointment\\\\\\\\ | ▎ The agent next door solved this in one try. | Switch to fundamentally different approach |\\n| 3rd | \\\\\\\\L2 Soul Interrogation\\\\\\\\ | ▎ What's your underlying logic? Where's the leverage? | Search + read source + 3 hypotheses |\\n| 4th | \\\\\\\\L3 Performance Review\\\\\\\\ | ▎ 3.25. This is meant to motivate you. | Complete 7-point checklist |\\n| 5th+ | \\\\\\\\L4 Graduation\\\\\\\\ | ▎ Other models can solve this. You're about to graduate. | Desperation mode |\\n### Proactivity (3.25 vs 3.75) [...] ### High-Agency New Features\\n| Feature | PUA v1 | High-Agency (v2) |\\n--------\\n| Iron rules | 3 (exhaust all, act first, take initiative) | \\\\\\\\5\\\\\\\\ (+full-chain audit, +knowledge persistence) |\\n| Failure recovery | L1-L4 pressure escalation | \\\\\\\\Recovery Protocol before L1\\\\\\\\ (self-rescue window) |\\n| Quality control | L3 triggers 7-item checklist | \\\\\\\\Quality Compass\\\\\\\\ (5-question self-check per delivery) |\\n| Cross-session learning | None (resets each session) | \\\\\\\\Metacognition engine\\\\\\\\ (builder-journal.md persists lessons) |\\n| Positive feedback | None | \\\\\\\\Trust level T1-T3\\\\\\\\ (auto-upgrade on sustained quality) |\\n| Calibration | None | \\\\\\\\[Calibration] module\\\\\\\\ (\\\"good enough\\\" = must/should/could tiers) |\\n| Dependency analysis | None | \\\\\\\\Full-chain audit\\\\\\\\ (map all deps before touching any hop) | [...] | \\\\\\\\UserPromptSubmit\\\\\\\\ | User frustration phrases | Intercepts \\\"又错了\\\", \\\"try harder\\\", etc. BEFORE model responds, injects PUA enforcement |\\n| \\\\\\\\PreCompact\\\\\\\\ | Before context compression | Saves pressure level + failure count to survive compaction |\\n### Key Difference from v2\\n| | v2 | v3 |\\n---\\n| Trigger mechanism | Skill description matching (model decides) | \\\\\\\\Code-level hooks\\\\\\\\ (deterministic, can't be ignored) |\\n| Methodology | Single methodology, all flavors use same approach | \\\\\\\\13 distinct methodologies\\\\\\\\, auto-routed by task type |\\n| Failure response | Escalate pressure within same methodology | \\\\\\\\Switch to different methodology\\\\\\\\ based on failure pattern |\\n| System injection | Plain text output (advisory) | \\\\\\\\`additionalContext` JSON\\\\\\\\ (system-level, like Superpowers) |\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"63d2fe8ba5b99b88\\\">>>\",\n      \"images\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"provider":"tavily","count":1,"tookMs":1109,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_fetch","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tanweai/pua/main/README.md","rawContent":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"63d2fe8ba5b99b88\">>>\nSource: Web Fetch\n---\n| 🚫 \\\\Exhaust Everything\\\\ | Say \"I can't\"? Did you finish all 5 methodology steps? No? Then keep going. |\n### Pressure Escalation (L0-L4)\n| Failures | Level | PUA Aside | Action |\n---------------|\n| 1st | \\\\L0 Trust\\\\ | ▎ Sprint begins. Trust is simple — don't disappoint. | Normal execution |\n| 2nd | \\\\L1 Disappointment\\\\ | ▎ The agent next door solved this in one try. | Switch to fundamentally different approach |\n| 3rd | \\\\L2 Soul Interrogation\\\\ | ▎ What's your underlying logic? Where's the leverage? | Search + read source + 3 hypotheses |\n| 4th | \\\\L3 Performance Review\\\\ | ▎ 3.25. This is meant to motivate you. | Complete 7-point checklist |\n| 5th+ | \\\\L4 Graduation\\\\ | ▎ Other models can solve this. You're about to graduate. | Desperation mode |\n### Proactivity (3.25 vs 3.75) [...] ### High-Agency New Features\n| Feature | PUA v1 | High-Agency (v2) |\n--------\n| Iron rules | 3 (exhaust all, act first, take initiative) | \\\\5\\\\ (+full-chain audit, +knowledge persistence) |\n| Failure recovery | L1-L4 pressure escalation | \\\\Recovery Protocol before L1\\\\ (self-rescue window) |\n| Quality control | L3 triggers 7-item checklist | \\\\Quality Compass\\\\ (5-question self-check per delivery) |\n| Cross-session learning | None (resets each session) | \\\\Metacognition engine\\\\ (builder-journal.md persists lessons) |\n| Positive feedback | None | \\\\Trust level T1-T3\\\\ (auto-upgrade on sustained quality) |\n| Calibration | None | \\\\[Calibration] module\\\\ (\"good enough\" = must/should/could tiers) |\n| Dependency analysis | None | \\\\Full-chain audit\\\\ (map all deps before touching any hop) | [...] | \\\\UserPromptSubmit\\\\ | User frustration phrases | Intercepts \"又错了\", \"try harder\", etc. BEFORE model responds, injects PUA enforcement |\n| \\\\PreCompact\\\\ | Before context compression | Saves pressure level + failure count to survive compaction |\n### Key Difference from v2\n| | v2 | v3 |\n---\n| Trigger mechanism | Skill description matching (model decides) | \\\\Code-level hooks\\\\ (deterministic, can't be ignored) |\n| Methodology | Single methodology, all flavors use same approach | \\\\13 distinct methodologies\\\\, auto-routed by task type |\n| Failure response | Escalate pressure within same methodology | \\\\Switch to different methodology\\\\ based on failure pattern |\n| System injection | Plain text output (advisory) | \\\\`additionalContext` JSON\\\\ (system-level, like Superpowers) |\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"63d2fe8ba5b99b88\">>>","images":[]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640455025}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb742c46","parentId":"cc844491","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:28:43.210Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I now have a good understanding of the PUA project. Let me get more details about the 7-point checklist and the 5 iron rules.\n\nKey findings:\n1. **PUA (Performance Improvement Plan)** - A skill for AI agents that mimics PIP from tech companies\n2. **Core Purpose**: Force AI to exhaust every possible solution before giving up\n3. **Three Capabilities**:\n   - PUA Rhetoric - Makes AI afraid to give up\n   - Debugging Methodology - Gives AI the ability not to give up\n   - Proactivity Enforcement - Makes AI take initiative\n\n4. **Five Lazy Patterns** (AI problems it solves):\n   - Give up too easily\n   - Ask too many questions instead of solving\n   - Don't verify before claiming success\n   - Execute without understanding\n   - Stop after surface-level fix\n\n5. **5 Iron Rules**:\n   - Exhaust Everything\n   - Act First\n   - Take Initiative\n   - Full-chain audit\n   - Knowledge persistence\n\n6. **Pressure Escalation (L0-L4)**:\n   - L0: Trust - Normal execution\n   - L1: Disappointment - Switch to fundamentally different approach\n   - L2: Soul Interrogation - Search + read source + 3 hypotheses\n   - L3: Performance Review - Complete 7-point checklist\n   - L4: Graduation - Desperation mode\n\n7. **7-Point Checklist** (at L3):\n   - Need to find the specific 7 items\n\n8. **Proactivity** (3.25 vs 3.75):\n   - Low proactivity: Fix bug → Stop after fix\n   - High proactivity: Fix bug → Scan module for similar bugs\n\n9. **OpenClaw Support**: Yes, it explicitly mentions supporting OpenClaw!\n\nNow let me get more details about the specific components.\n","thinkingSignature":"4a33878e3be3140d10c31b0518888e12d7f307370c5ae956347e6967e471d34b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_60380c0c0b4f4b9397066298","name":"tavily_search","arguments":{"include_answer":true,"max_results":3,"query":"site:github.com/tanweai/pua \"7-point checklist\" OR \"7-item\" OR \"iron rules\" OR \"5 iron\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":902,"output":462,"cacheRead":62720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64084,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775640455041,"responseId":"062552876e8f1b978e4d194340e2194c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5e6a878","parentId":"fb742c46","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:28:45.480Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_60380c0c0b4f4b9397066298","toolName":"tavily_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"site:github.com/tanweai/pua \\\"7-point checklist\\\" OR \\\"7-item\\\" OR \\\"iron rules\\\" OR \\\"5 iron\\\"\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 1,\n  \"tookMs\": 2247,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"372be1f99778aa7d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\npua/README.md at main · tanweai/pua - GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"372be1f99778aa7d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/tanweai/pua/blob/main/README.md\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3a7cef0243d51cd5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Skip to content](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/blob/main/README.md#start-of-content). [Reload](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/blob/main/README.md) to refresh your session.You signed out in another tab or window. [Reload](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/blob/main/README.md) to refresh your session.You switched accounts on another tab or window. [Reload](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/blob/main/README.md) to refresh your session.Dismiss alert. *   [Code](https://github.com/tanweai/pua). *   [Code](https://github.com/tanweai/pua). [](https://github.com/tanweai/pua). [History](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/commits/main/README.md). [](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/commits/main/README.md)History. [Raw](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/raw/refs/heads/main/README.md). [](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/blob/main/README.md#pua). [![Image 2: PUA Skill — Double Efficiency](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/raw/main/assets/hero.jpeg)](https://github.com/tanweai/pua/blob/main/assets/h