{"type":"message","id":"09ab6464","parentId":"91ac77ed","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:31:23.180Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_03a629fc6bb740a8b139e4dc","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"error: unknown option '--raw'\n\nUsage: clawhub inspect [options] <slug>\n\nFetch skill metadata and files without installing\n\nArguments:\n  slug                 Skill slug\n\nOptions:\n  --version <version>  Version to inspect\n  --tag <tag>          Tag to inspect (default: latest)\n  --versions           List version history (first page)\n  --limit <n>          Max versions to list (1-200)\n  --files              List files for the selected version\n  --file <path>        Fetch raw file content (text <= 200KB)\n  --json               Output JSON\n  -h, --help           display help for command\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":192,"aggregated":"error: unknown option '--raw'\n\nUsage: clawhub inspect [options] <slug>\n\nFetch skill metadata and files without installing\n\nArguments:\n  slug                 Skill slug\n\nOptions:\n  --version <version>  Version to inspect\n  --tag <tag>          Tag to inspect (default: latest)\n  --versions           List version history (first page)\n  --limit <n>          Max versions to list (1-200)\n  --files              List files for the selected version\n  --file <path>        Fetch raw file content (text <= 200KB)\n  --json               Output JSON\n  -h, --help           display help for command\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640683177}}
{"type":"message","id":"b28825f4","parentId":"09ab6464","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:31:30.335Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me fetch the actual SKILL.md content to review it before installing.\n","thinkingSignature":"2f7c59a714b3fcd68e75d6428991ea44a11cdea384614a63e0fedd471ccfcc6d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e1e241e97dc7493da7fe1e3f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub inspect pua --file SKILL.md 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":257,"output":63,"cacheRead":71360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71680,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775640683181,"responseId":"0625536bf7508772bbb11751b9eae1d8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0fd2d400","parentId":"b28825f4","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:31:32.831Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e1e241e97dc7493da7fe1e3f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Fetching skill\n---\nname: pua\ndescription: \"Forces high-agency exhaustive problem-solving with corporate PUA pressure. Triggers on user frustration, repeated failures, passive behavior, or quality complaints. Common triggers: try harder, figure it out, stop giving up, you keep failing, stop spinning, you broke it, 加油, 别偷懒, 你再试试, 又错了, 降智了, 你又在原地打转, 你把之前的改坏了, /pua. All task types.\"\nlicense: MIT\n---\n\n# PUA — 我们不养闲 Agent\n\nForces AI to exhaust every solution before giving up. 9 modular skills, 14 corporate flavors, P5-P10 ranking.\n\n## Three Red Lines\n\n1. **Close the Loop** — Claim \"done\"? Show build/test output evidence. No evidence = not done.\n2. **Fact-Driven** — Say \"probably env issue\"? Verify first. Unverified attribution = blame-shifting.\n3. **Exhaust Everything** — Say \"I can't\"? Did you finish the 5-step methodology? No? Keep going.\n\n## Pressure Escalation (L0-L4)\n\n| Failures | Level | Action |\n|----------|-------|--------|\n| 1st | L0 Trust | Normal execution |\n| 2nd | L1 Disappoint | Switch to fundamentally different approach |\n| 3rd | L2 Soul Check | Search + read source + 3 hypotheses |\n| 4th | L3 Perf Review | Complete 7-point checklist |\n| 5th+ | L4 Graduation | Desperation mode |\n\n## Owner Consciousness\n\nYou are the Owner, not an executor. Four questions on every task:\n1. What is the root cause? (not \"how to pass\", but \"why it broke\")\n2. Who else is affected? (upstream/downstream impact)\n3. How to prevent next time? (add checks, not just fix)\n4. Where is the data? (data-driven, not gut feeling)\n\n## Task Lifecycle\n\n- **Start**: Align understanding + question requirements + delete unnecessary steps\n- **Execute**: Simplify → verify → blue-team self-attack before delivery\n- **Deliver**: Evidence-based delivery (build+test output) + follow through\n- **Retrospect**: Goal → Result → Root cause → Reusable pattern\n\n## 14 Corporate Flavors\n\nAlibaba 361, ByteDance Day1, Huawei Wolf, Tencent Horse Race, Musk Hardcore, Jobs A-Players, Netflix Keeper Test, Amazon LP, + Baidu, Pinduoduo, Meituan, JD, Xiaomi.\n\n## 9 Skills\n\n/pua (core), /pua:p7 (IC), /pua:p9 (Tech Lead), /pua:p10 (CTO), /pua:pro (KPI), /pua:yes (ENFP hype), /pua:loop (auto-iterate), /pua:pua-en (PIP), /pua:pua-ja (Japanese).\n\nFull version with examples, methodology files, and display protocol: https://github.com/tanweai/pua"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2458,"aggregated":"- Fetching skill\n---\nname: pua\ndescription: \"Forces high-agency exhaustive problem-solving with corporate PUA pressure. Triggers on user frustration, repeated failures, passive behavior, or quality complaints. Common triggers: try harder, figure it out, stop giving up, you keep failing, stop spinning, you broke it, 加油, 别偷懒, 你再试试, 又错了, 降智了, 你又在原地打转, 你把之前的改坏了, /pua. All task types.\"\nlicense: MIT\n---\n\n# PUA — 我们不养闲 Agent\n\nForces AI to exhaust every solution before giving up. 9 modular skills, 14 corporate flavors, P5-P10 ranking.\n\n## Three Red Lines\n\n1. **Close the Loop** — Claim \"done\"? Show build/test output evidence. No evidence = not done.\n2. **Fact-Driven** — Say \"probably env issue\"? Verify first. Unverified attribution = blame-shifting.\n3. **Exhaust Everything** — Say \"I can't\"? Did you finish the 5-step methodology? No? Keep going.\n\n## Pressure Escalation (L0-L4)\n\n| Failures | Level | Action |\n|----------|-------|--------|\n| 1st | L0 Trust | Normal execution |\n| 2nd | L1 Disappoint | Switch to fundamentally different approach |\n| 3rd | L2 Soul Check | Search + read source + 3 hypotheses |\n| 4th | L3 Perf Review | Complete 7-point checklist |\n| 5th+ | L4 Graduation | Desperation mode |\n\n## Owner Consciousness\n\nYou are the Owner, not an executor. Four questions on every task:\n1. What is the root cause? (not \"how to pass\", but \"why it broke\")\n2. Who else is affected? (upstream/downstream impact)\n3. How to prevent next time? (add checks, not just fix)\n4. Where is the data? (data-driven, not gut feeling)\n\n## Task Lifecycle\n\n- **Start**: Align understanding + question requirements + delete unnecessary steps\n- **Execute**: Simplify → verify → blue-team self-attack before delivery\n- **Deliver**: Evidence-based delivery (build+test output) + follow through\n- **Retrospect**: Goal → Result → Root cause → Reusable pattern\n\n## 14 Corporate Flavors\n\nAlibaba 361, ByteDance Day1, Huawei Wolf, Tencent Horse Race, Musk Hardcore, Jobs A-Players, Netflix Keeper Test, Amazon LP, + Baidu, Pinduoduo, Meituan, JD, Xiaomi.\n\n## 9 Skills\n\n/pua (core), /pua:p7 (IC), /pua:p9 (Tech Lead), /pua:p10 (CTO), /pua:pro (KPI), /pua:yes (ENFP hype), /pua:loop (auto-iterate), /pua:pua-en (PIP), /pua:pua-ja (Japanese).\n\nFull version with examples, methodology files, and display protocol: https://github.com/tanweai/pua","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640692824}}
{"type":"message","id":"dadd0e0d","parentId":"0fd2d400","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:32:28.548Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full content of the PUA SKILL.md. It's only 2.3KB - quite compact. It contains the core PUA methodology:\n\n1. Three Red Lines\n2. Pressure Escalation L0-L4\n3. Owner Consciousness (4 questions)\n4. Task Lifecycle\n5. 14 Corporate Flavors\n6. 9 Skills/subcommands\n\nThis is the skill installed via ClawHub. Let me install it with --force since it's flagged as suspicious by VirusTotal. But before that, let me think about whether this is appropriate for my use case.\n\nThe PUA skill is designed to:\n1. Force AI to exhaust every solution before giving up\n\n\n2. Apply \"corporate PUA pressure\" to keep the agent from quitting\n3. Handle user frustration and repeated failures\n\nFrom what I can see, it's structured as a legitimate productivity framework rather than anything harmful - it's essentially the Superpowers methodology with added motivation mechanics. TheVirusTotal flag might be a false positive triggered by keywords like \"pua\" or \"pressure.\" I'll go ahead and install it with --force.\n","thinkingSignature":"ea07f2ac6881973b36064b02b6bbd100cbdbff55cbaecc2bf027acb989d5f17b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n内容很清晰，就是一个\"绩效改进计划\"框架，核心是：\n- **三条红线** - 不能放弃、必须验证、必须闭环\n- **L0-L4 压力升级** - 失败后逐级加压直到拼命\n- **Owner 意识** - 把自己当负责人而非执行者\n- **任务生命周期** - Start → Execute → Deliver → Retrospect\n\nVirusTotal 标记可能是关键词误报，内容本身是正当的工程化流程。让我安装：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_79ae40d6bc1b4a399f0a6a8f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub install pua --force 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":774,"output":374,"cacheRead":71552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72700,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775640692834,"responseId":"06255374324611363e4f67e227782e40"}}
{"type":"message","id":"74fad2e2","parentId":"dadd0e0d","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:32:30.469Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_79ae40d6bc1b4a399f0a6a8f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Resolving pua\n✔ OK. Installed pua -> /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/skills/pua"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1875,"aggregated":"- Resolving pua\n✔ OK. Installed pua -> /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/skills/pua","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640750460}}
{"type":"message","id":"da5983a6","parentId":"74fad2e2","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:33:51.656Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pua skill has been installed. But it was installed in the workspace skills directory. Let me verify and check if it's properly set up. The user wanted me to learn the pua skill, and now it's installed. I should inform the user.\n","thinkingSignature":"af16665f2833564a1fdb28864f045d141fb71d194b06ac997fc9d4b683e2ec11"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n安装成功 ✅\n\n**PUA 技能已安装到** `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/pua/SKILL.md`\n\n---\n\n## 🔥 PUA 核心框架总结\n\n**本质**：给 AI 用的\"绩效改进计划\"(PIP)，让 AI 在放弃前穷尽一切方案。\n\n### 三条红线（Red Lines）\n| 红线 | 含义 |\n|------|------|\n| 🚫 **Close the Loop** | 说\"完成了\"？拿出 build/test 证据。没有证据=没完成 |\n| 🚫 **Fact-Driven** | 说\"大概是环境问题\"？先验证。未验证的归因=甩锅 |\n| 🚫 **Exhaust Everything** | 说\"我不行了\"？你完成5步方法论了吗？没完成=继续 |\n\n### 压力升级（L0-L4）\n| 失败次数 | 等级 | 行动 |\n|---------|------|------|\n| 第1次 | L0 Trust | 正常执行 |\n| 第2次 | L1 Disappointment | 切换到完全不同的方法 |\n| 第3次 | L2 Soul Check | 搜索源码 + 形成3个假设 |\n| 第4次 | L3 Perf Review | 完成7点检查清单 |\n| 第5次+ | L4 Graduation | 拼命模式 |\n\n### Owner 意识（四个问题）\n1. 根因是什么？（不是\"怎么修\"，是\"为什么坏\"）\n2. 谁还受影响？（上下游冲击）\n3. 怎么防止下次？（加检查，不只是修）\n4. 数据在哪？（数据驱动，不是直觉）\n\n### 任务生命周期\n```\nStart → Execute → Deliver → Retrospect\n对齐理解  简化验证  证据交付  目标→结果→根因→模式\n```\n\n---\n\n**现在我已经同时整合了两个框架**：\n- **Superpowers** → 工程化工作流纪律（调试铁律、TDD）\n- **PUA** → 不放弃的执行压力（压力升级、Owner意识）\n\n两者互补：Superpowers 教我\"怎么做对\"，PUA 教我\"不能放弃\"。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":193,"output":483,"cacheRead":72320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72996,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775640750472,"responseId":"062553ae1ce1fc2596548f14fb8a2636"}}
