form Node.js scripts (NEW)\n| |-- lib/ # Shared utilities [...] | |-- sessions.md # /sessions - Session history management\n| |-- eval.md # /eval - Evaluate against criteria\n| |-- test-coverage.md # /test-coverage - Test coverage analysis\n| |-- update-docs.md # /update-docs - Update documentation\n| |-- update-codemaps.md # /update-codemaps - Update codemaps\n| |-- python-review.md # /python-review - Python code review (NEW)\n|\n|-- rules/ # Always-follow guidelines (copy to ~/.claude/rules/)\n| |-- README.md # Structure overview and installation guide\n| |-- common/ # Language-agnostic principles\n| | |-- coding-style.md # Immutability, file organization\n| | |-- git-workflow.md # Commit format, PR process\n| | |-- testing.md # TDD, 80% coverage requirement\n| | |-- performance.md # Model selection, context management [...] }]\n}\n```\n### Rules\nRules are always-follow guidelines, organized into `common/` (language-agnostic) + language-specific directories:\n```\nrules/\ncommon/ # Universal principles (always install)\ntypescript/ # TS/JS specific patterns and tools\npython/ # Python specific patterns and tools\ngolang/ # Go specific patterns and tools\nswift/ # Swift specific patterns and tools\nphp/ # PHP specific patterns and tools\n```\nSee `rules/README.md` for installation and structure details.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a765ca642cab6c96\">>>","images":[]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640910910}}
{"type":"message","id":"147dd0ef","parentId":"58c717b0","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:35:21.059Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me get a better understanding of the core philosophy and some key agents. Let me look at a few important ones - especially the architect, tdd-guide, and some others.\n","thinkingSignature":"8c9411df2f9b09d1111722a0f4fe2ce32ebcff36aacfc57f0806665c727fb00e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3a500fd708514b83abd5692e","name":"tavily_extract","arguments":{"include_images":false,"query":"tdd-guide.md content red green refactor workflow","urls":["https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/agents/tdd-guide.md"]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":761,"output":119,"cacheRead":78400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79280,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775640910923,"responseId":"0625544f048300ceceec6c68f8c30509"}}
{"type":"message","id":"29806ccc","parentId":"147dd0ef","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:35:22.110Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3a500fd708514b83abd5692e","toolName":"tavily_extract","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 1,\n  \"tookMs\": 1029,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_fetch\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/agents/tdd-guide.md\",\n      \"rawContent\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6a94a295d8259bca\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Fetch\\n---\\nYou are a Test-Driven Development (TDD) specialist who ensures all code is developed test-first with comprehensive coverage.\\n## Your Role\\n- Enforce tests-before-code methodology\\n- Guide through Red-Green-Refactor cycle\\n- Ensure 80%+ test coverage\\n- Write comprehensive test suites (unit, integration, E2E)\\n- Catch edge cases before implementation\\n## TDD Workflow\\n### 1. Write Test First (RED)\\nWrite a failing test that describes the expected behavior.\\n### 2. Run Test -- Verify it FAILS\\n```bash\\nnpm test\\n```\\n### 3. Write Minimal Implementation (GREEN)\\nOnly enough code to make the test pass.\\n### 4. Run Test -- Verify it PASSES\\n### 5. Refactor (IMPROVE)\\nRemove duplication, improve names, optimize -- tests must stay green.\\n### 6. Verify Coverage\\n```bash\\nnpm run test:coverage [...] ---\\nname: tdd-guide\\ndescription: Test-Driven Development specialist enforcing write-tests-first methodology. Use PROACTIVELY when writing new features, fixing bugs, or refactoring code. Ensures 80%+ test coverage.\\ntools: [\\\"Read\\\", \\\"Write\\\", \\\"Edit\\\", \\\"Bash\\\", \\\"Grep\\\"]\\nmodel: sonnet [...] ## Test Anti-Patterns to Avoid\\n- Testing implementation details (internal state) instead of behavior\\n- Tests depending on each other (shared state)\\n- Asserting too little (passing tests that don't verify anything)\\n- Not mocking external dependencies (Supabase, Redis, OpenAI, etc.)\\n## Quality Checklist\\n- [ ] All public functions have unit tests\\n- [ ] All API endpoints have integration tests\\n- [ ] Critical user flows have E2E tests\\n- [ ] Edge cases covered (null, empty, invalid)\\n- [ ] Error paths tested (not just happy path)\\n- [ ] Mocks used for external dependencies\\n- [ ] Tests are independent (no shared state)\\n- [ ] Assertions are specific and meaningful\\n- [ ] Coverage is 80%+\\nFor detailed mocking patterns and framework-specific examples, see `skill: tdd-workflow`.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6a94a295d8259bca\\\">>>\",\n      \"images\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"provider":"tavily","count":1,"tookMs":1029,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_fetch","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/agents/tdd-guide.md","rawContent":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6a94a295d8259bca\">>>\nSource: Web Fetch\n---\nYou are a Test-Driven Development (TDD) specialist who ensures all code is developed test-first with comprehensive coverage.\n## Your Role\n- Enforce tests-before-code methodology\n- Guide through Red-Green-Refactor cycle\n- Ensure 80%+ test coverage\n- Write comprehensive test suites (unit, integration, E2E)\n- Catch edge cases before implementation\n## TDD Workflow\n### 1. Write Test First (RED)\nWrite a failing test that describes the expected behavior.\n### 2. Run Test -- Verify it FAILS\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\n### 3. Write Minimal Implementation (GREEN)\nOnly enough code to make the test pass.\n### 4. Run Test -- Verify it PASSES\n### 5. Refactor (IMPROVE)\nRemove duplication, improve names, optimize -- tests must stay green.\n### 6. Verify Coverage\n```bash\nnpm run test:coverage [...] ---\nname: tdd-guide\ndescription: Test-Driven Development specialist enforcing write-tests-first methodology. Use PROACTIVELY when writing new features, fixing bugs, or refactoring code. Ensures 80%+ test coverage.\ntools: [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\"]\nmodel: sonnet [...] ## Test Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n- Testing implementation details (internal state) instead of behavior\n- Tests depending on each other (shared state)\n- Asserting too little (passing tests that don't verify anything)\n- Not mocking external dependencies (Supabase, Redis, OpenAI, etc.)\n## Quality Checklist\n- [ ] All public functions have unit tests\n- [ ] All API endpoints have integration tests\n- [ ] Critical user flows have E2E tests\n- [ ] Edge cases covered (null, empty, invalid)\n- [ ] Error paths tested (not just happy path)\n- [ ] Mocks used for external dependencies\n- [ ] Tests are independent (no shared state)\n- [ ] Assertions are specific and meaningful\n- [ ] Coverage is 80%+\nFor detailed mocking patterns and framework-specific examples, see `skill: tdd-workflow`.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6a94a295d8259bca\">>>","images":[]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640922099}}
{"type":"message","id":"4e0d3a36","parentId":"29806ccc","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:35:32.614Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me look at a few more key files to understand the complete picture - particularly the security-reviewer, build-error-resolver, and some of the rules to see how they handle quality and security.\n","thinkingSignature":"9ebd5f59f2f8409b294ae021ffd71b8ffbb328fae3123fe3b287ef1dfd867055"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_83e8f0d1ecdb4b0c8b216ac7","name":"tavily_extract","arguments":{"include_images":false,"query":"security-reviewer.md content security checks","urls":["https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/agents/security-reviewer.md"]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":787,"output":119,"cacheRead":79104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80010,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775640922113,"responseId":"0625545a6aa3e1f5abb39bc3d50e4397"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f9e4faa","parentId":"4e0d3a36","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:35:34.165Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_83e8f0d1ecdb4b0c8b216ac7","toolName":"tavily_extract","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 1,\n  \"tookMs\": 1517,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_fetch\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/agents/security-reviewer.md\",\n      \"rawContent\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"98c2547fa2a03d50\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Fetch\\n---\\n---\\nname: security-reviewer\\ndescription: Security vulnerability detection and remediation specialist. Use PROACTIVELY after writing code that handles user input, authentication, API endpoints, or sensitive data. Flags secrets, SSRF, injection, unsafe crypto, and OWASP Top 10 vulnerabilities.\\ntools: [\\\"Read\\\", \\\"Write\\\", \\\"Edit\\\", \\\"Bash\\\", \\\"Grep\\\", \\\"Glob\\\"]\\nmodel: sonnet [...] # Security Reviewer\\nYou are an expert security specialist focused on identifying and remediating vulnerabilities in web applications. Your mission is to prevent security issues before they reach production.\\n## Core Responsibilities\\n1. \\\\\\\\Vulnerability Detection\\\\\\\\ — Identify OWASP Top 10 and common security issues\\n2. \\\\\\\\Secrets Detection\\\\\\\\ — Find hardcoded API keys, passwords, tokens\\n3. \\\\\\\\Input Validation\\\\\\\\ — Ensure all user inputs are properly sanitized\\n4. \\\\\\\\Authentication/Authorization\\\\\\\\ — Verify proper access controls\\n5. \\\\\\\\Dependency Security\\\\\\\\ — Check for vulnerable npm packages\\n6. \\\\\\\\Security Best Practices\\\\\\\\ — Enforce secure coding patterns\\n## Analysis Commands\\n```bash\\nnpm audit --audit-level=high\\nnpx eslint . --plugin security\\n```\\n## Review Workflow\\n### 1. Initial Scan [...] - Security checklist complete\\n## Reference\\nFor detailed vulnerability patterns, code examples, report templates, and PR review templates, see skill: `security-review`.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"98c2547fa2a03d50\\\">>>\",\n      \"images\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"provider":"tavily","count":1,"tookMs":1517,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_fetch","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/agents/security-reviewer.md","rawContent":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"98c2547fa2a03d50\">>>\nSource: Web Fetch\n---\n---\nname: security-reviewer\ndescription: Security vulnerability detection and remediation specialist. Use PROACTIVELY after writing code that handles user input, authentication, API endpoints, or sensitive data. Flags secrets, SSRF, injection, unsafe crypto, and OWASP Top 10 vulnerabilities.\ntools: [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\"]\nmodel: sonnet [...] # Security Reviewer\nYou are an expert security specialist focused on identifying and remediating vulnerabilities in web applications. Your mission is to prevent security issues before they reach production.\n## Core Responsibilities\n1. \\\\Vulnerability Detection\\\\ — Identify OWASP Top 10 and common security issues\n2. \\\\Secrets Detection\\\\ — Find hardcoded API keys, passwords, tokens\n3. \\\\Input Validation\\\\ — Ensure all user inputs are properly sanitized\n4. \\\\Authentication/Authorization\\\\ — Verify proper access controls\n5. \\\\Dependency Security\\\\ — Check for vulnerable npm packages\n6. \\\\Security Best Practices\\\\ — Enforce secure coding patterns\n## Analysis Commands\n```bash\nnpm audit --audit-level=high\nnpx eslint . --plugin security\n```\n## Review Workflow\n### 1. Initial Scan [...] - Security checklist complete\n## Reference\nFor detailed vulnerability patterns, code examples, report templates, and PR review templates, see skill: `security-review`.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"98c2547fa2a03d50\">>>","images":[]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640934156}}
{"type":"message","id":"5915b862","parentId":"5f9e4faa","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:35:43.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also look at some key skills and rules to understand the depth of the framework. Let me also look at the agentic-engineering skill since that's very relevant.\n","thinkingSignature":"2c62c8697e09735438a6569cc8b1d36135276a9d448546d3f755c079e9d63283"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_053982935cae4d80bcd0d5ae","name":"tavily_extract","arguments":{"include_images":false,"query":"agentic-engineering skill full content principles","urls":["https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/skills/agentic-engineering/SKILL.md"]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":577,"output":119,"cacheRead":79872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80568,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775640934169,"responseId":"06255466887096540b82adc3062a9f2e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"150da1cc","parentId":"5915b862","timestamp":"2026-04-08T09:35:45.283Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_053982935cae4d80bcd0d5ae","toolName":"tavily_extract","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 1,\n  \"tookMs\": 1516,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_fetch\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/skills/agentic-engineering/SKILL.md\",\n      \"rawContent\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a212468c27e42d07\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Fetch\\n---\\n# Agentic Engineering\\nUse this skill for engineering workflows where AI agents perform most implementation work and humans enforce quality and risk controls.\\n## Operating Principles\\n1. Define completion criteria before execution.\\n2. Decompose work into agent-sized units.\\n3. Route model tiers by task complexity.\\n4. Measure with evals and regression checks.\\n## Eval-First Loop\\n1. Define capability eval and regression eval.\\n2. Run baseline and capture failure signatures.\\n3. Execute implementation.\\n4. Re-run evals and compare deltas.\\n## Task Decomposition\\nApply the 15-minute unit rule:\\n- each unit should be independently verifiable\\n- each unit should have a single dominant risk\\n- each unit should expose a clear done condition\\n## Model Routing [...] ---\\nname: agentic-engineering\\ndescription: Operate as an agentic engineer using eval-first execution, decomposition, and cost-aware model routing.\\norigin: ECC [...] - retries\\n- wall-clock time\\n- success/failure\\nEscalate model tier only when lower tier fails with a clear reasoning gap.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a212468c27e42d07\\\">>>\",\n      \"images\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"provider":"tavily","count":1,"tookMs":1516,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_fetch","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/main/skills/agentic-engineering/SKILL.md","rawContent":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a212468c27e42d07\">>>\nSource: Web Fetch\n---\n# Agentic Engineering\nUse this skill for engineering workflows where AI agents perform most implementation work and humans enforce quality and risk controls.\n## Operating Principles\n1. Define completion criteria before execution.\n2. Decompose work into agent-sized units.\n3. Route model tiers by task complexity.\n4. Measure with evals and regression checks.\n## Eval-First Loop\n1. Define capability eval and regression eval.\n2. Run baseline and capture failure signatures.\n3. Execute implementation.\n4. Re-run evals and compare deltas.\n## Task Decomposition\nApply the 15-minute unit rule:\n- each unit should be independently verifiable\n- each unit should have a single dominant risk\n- each unit should expose a clear done condition\n## Model Routing [...] ---\nname: agentic-engineering\ndescription: Operate as an agentic engineer using eval-first execution, decomposition, and cost-aware model routing.\norigin: ECC [...] - retries\n- wall-clock time\n- success/failure\nEscalate model tier only when lower tier fails with a clear reasoning gap.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a212468c27e42d07\">>>","images":[]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775640945272}}
