{"type":"message","id":"b54cd1a5","parentId":"007ceaad","timestamp":"2026-04-08T17:20:51.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very interesting. Looking at the walk-forward results:\n\n1. In-sample (train) performance: -3.23% annual return, Sharpe -0.291\n2. Out-of-sample (test) performance: 27.97% annual return, Sharpe 0.822\n\nThis is inverted! The test set performs much better than the train set. This is highly suspicious and indicates likely data leakage or some other serious issue. A strategy shouldn't perform better on unseen data than on seen data.\n\nNow I have enough information to write a comprehensive audit report. Let me gather a few more details about the execution and risk modules.\n","thinkingSignature":"7b9ae261948b9d16b804aca7ba7e6df117317dbcbfd82eb6c3813258ae87ec5a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cboi6pl7bzfp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && ls -la research/reports/ | tail -20","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cboi6pl7bzfp_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && cat research/reports/live_execution_brief_v1_20260408.md 2>/dev/null | head -50","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":549,"output":261,"cacheRead":64400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65210,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775668843957,"responseId":"0625c16caaf8f60a3815daa81c1009ad"}}
